{"TopicId":110719,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"My Simpit Project","CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-24T23:41:00Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-15T17:01:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh man, that is amazing!!!\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m seriously\u00A0drooling all over my keyboard... lol.....\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Freshmeat","CreatedById":111048,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T11:17:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222362672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452830183\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krewmember\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 15/1/2016 at 4:56 AM, Krewmember said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally some progress to report! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI installed the glare shield, and the multi-function display on the commanders side \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E, the monitor still needs a bezel but that\u0027s still in the works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;snip awesome pictures\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProgress has been slow do to cold weather and a lack of supplies. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I\u0027m hoping to have the frame for the overhead done by spring. We\u0027ll see...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis flew under my radar. It is really cool. What do you use for display, is it KRPC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T16:50:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222363300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452876968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002283990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starwhip\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/15/2016 at 11:56 AM, Starwhip said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome! I love how much data fits on the screen. Personally, I say readouts cluttered with info are the best kind. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. And since I\u0027m probably going to have 3 monitors for displaying info\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222363304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452877272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/15/2016 at 0:01 PM, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh man, that is amazing!!!\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m seriously\u00A0drooling all over my keyboard... lol.....\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks man \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222366287\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453029430\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Freshmeat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Freshmeat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis flew under my radar. It is really cool. What do you use for display, is it KRPC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, it\u0027s orbiter MEDs that I found and photoshopped onto a image the same resolution as the monitor \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E it\u0027s just for testing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have not had the time to get the software part of this project started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"richfiles","CreatedById":129946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-21T07:48:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222362672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452830183\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krewmember\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn January 15, 2016 at 9:56 PM, Krewmember said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally some progress to report! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI installed the glare shield, and the multi-function display on the commanders side \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E, the monitor still needs a bezel but that\u0027s still in the works.\u003Cbr\u003E\nProgress has been slow do to cold weather and a lack of supplies. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I\u0027m hoping to have the frame for the overhead done by spring. We\u0027ll see...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022arial, helvetica, sans-serif\u0022\u003EWow! I have no idea what you\u0027re using for that display, but it\u0027s impressive! That\u0027s gonna make one heck of a cockpit! Is that software on the computer, running off integrated an integrated graphics port, or is it a single board computer receiving telemetry? (\u003C/font\u003E**EDIT**\u00A0A fake telemetry readout in a fake spaceship cockpit! Le GASP! Can\u0027t wait to see it done for real!\u003Cfont face=\u0022arial, helvetica, sans-serif\u0022\u003E) Regardless, it looks very professional!\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cfont face=\u0022arial, helvetica, sans-serif\u0022\u003EAs for cold weather... I know how you feel. My own project has ground to a near stand still, as all my major wood and metal\u00A0working\u00A0tools reside in an unheated barn a town over,\u00A0and that is far too cold right now to be venturing that far away, for that amount of time, to do that kind of work!\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nFortunately, I\u00A0can still work on electronics, but cash flow has been slow, so parts are on a trickle supply. Furthermore, I\u0027ve been focusing almost all my spare project time on my mechanical keyboard. It\u0027ll be\u00A0only a couple weeks before the key caps show up, so it\u0027s a rush to finish by then.\u00A0Very excited about finishing\u00A0that project! It\u0027s oaky though... I\u0027m \u003Cem\u003Ereally\u003C/em\u003E just waiting for 1.1 to launch, and\u00A0for the mods to catch up to that... In the meantime, I\u0027m busy having too much fun playing Fallout 4.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI did have\u00A0a major setback with my own project, specifically the\u00A0FDAI (navball) controller. Turns out, an Arduino doesn\u0027t stand a CHANCE of communicating enough bits\u00A0over I2C,\u00A0or processing fast enough to control the raw data needed to feed the DACs at a sufficient rate to do the arbitrary waveform generation on 10 channels. one, \u003Cem\u003Emaybe\u003C/em\u003E two channels, sure, but not 10. Fortunately, someone suggested a cheap DAC that featured an independent voltage reference input that allows me to use the DACs as attenuators. Now I only need to make a hardware 400 Hz sine generator, and feed that into the attenuator DACs... I only need to update those (x10) at the rate KSP sends telemetry updates, not at 400 Hz x timebase resolution x 10. Far more manageable! The good news, is that once I\u0027m done with my keyboard, I think I\u0027ll go back to working on the FDAI controller. I need to actually BUILD the circuit... I\u0027ve got \u003Cem\u003Ealmost\u003C/em\u003E all the parts for it already. Focus, me! Focus!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe actual control panel itself has been untouched, cause the translucent synthetic paper (from Nekoosa paper products)\u00A0that\u00A0I plan to use for meter and control panel backlit panels... Is useless with a printer that doesn\u0027t print color well, anymore. When spring comes, I\u0027ll venture forth from my weather\u00A0shuttered doors, once again, and find a print shop. Too darn cold!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnyhow, very, VERY awesome build you have going on, and that \u0022glass cockpit\u0022 is looking mighty, mighty fine!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222363300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452876968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002283990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starwhip\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn January 15, 2016 at 10:56 AM, Starwhip said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fact that you have the Red Green show on greatly pleases me. I guess you really are a handyman if you can get that to work! XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0px;line-height:normal;font-family:\u0027Lucida Grande\u0027;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nWell, if the women don\u0027t find you handsome, they should at least find you handy!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe new plan for it is to get one of those cheap little Raspberry Pi Zero boards (the ones that are \u003Cem\u003Esuper\u003C/em\u003E cheap). I want to set it up to play animations of the IVA and mission control characters (Gene Kerman, etc) at random. If I can make that work, then I\u0027ll mount the CRT in portrait mode. It\u0027d be purely aesthetic. I don\u0027t know if it\u0027d even have any interactivity, other than a \u0022Coms\u0022 switch on the panel that will be able to turn it on or off.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat\u0027s one area where I plan to have non game switches to make it feel more \u0022space capsuley\u0022. The\u00A0various components of the system will each have their own unique power switches, with their own \u0022DC Bus\u0022 or \u0022AC Bus\u0022 supplies labeled (\u0022DC Bus A\u0022, \u0022AC Bus Aux\u0022, etc). I think it sounds like a cool, relatively \u0022immersive\u0022 plan.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-21T07:51:06Z\u0022 title=\u002201/21/2016 07:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by richfiles\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-11T21:22:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuick update! I have started working on the caution and warning matrix \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts made out of polystyrene.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222cW7U54.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/2cW7U54.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I marked out and cut a hole in the dashboard for it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lo1vdMa.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/lo1vdMa.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have also ordered some 5mm flat top LEDs and a MAX7219 matrix board. I will post a update as soon as i receive them \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShawn\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-11T21:22:42Z\u0022 title=\u002205/11/2016 09:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Krewmember\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ozymandias_the_Goat","CreatedById":159377,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-11T22:01:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLove it so far. Take the kids to space...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Freshmeat","CreatedById":111048,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-12T09:26:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice work. I have had problems with the MAX chips if the signal is over long wires, the DP pin would not reliably work. It might have been the batch I was working with, but I will recommend hooking up so you do not use it. You have plenty of pins to spare with your setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-12T14:24:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222576889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463045176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Freshmeat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Freshmeat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice work. I have had problems with the MAX chips if the signal is over long wires, the DP pin would not reliably work. It might have been the batch I was working with, but I will recommend hooking up so you do not use it. You have plenty of pins to spare with your setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the heads up, apparently the MAX7219 can cause electromagnetic interference so maybe that is why \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-12T14:25:14Z\u0022 title=\u002205/12/2016 02:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 12, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Krewmember\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-12T16:22:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe LEDs arrived in the mail today \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E so I will get busy soldering\u00A0them\u00A0together.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/QYdy3lf.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022QYdy3lf.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also glued the back of the annunciator on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ZpfAhis.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022ZpfAhis.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/eHDOnJ8.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022eHDOnJ8.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-12T18:19:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLEDs are glued in place \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/IMZh3DF.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022IMZh3DF.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/PFBoacM.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022PFBoacM.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stibbons","CreatedById":57865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T01:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222576889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463045176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Freshmeat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/12/2016 at 7:26 PM, Freshmeat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice work. I have had problems with the MAX chips if the signal is over long wires, the DP pin would not reliably work. It might have been the batch I was working with, but I will recommend hooking up so you do not use it. You have plenty of pins to spare with your setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s weird. How long are you talking about? My setup uses three MAX7219s chained together, and somewhere around 12 inches of ribbon cable from the board carrying the controllers to the display boards. Only problems I\u0027ve had were purely user error.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222577647\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463077147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krewmember\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/12/2016 at 4:19 AM, Krewmember said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLEDs are glued in place \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking good!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T15:48:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222582382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463275454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257865\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022stibbons\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, stibbons said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking good!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did get the LEDs soldered together. but I hooked up the MAX7219 wrong and let the magic smoke out of the chip \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/VrFWER5.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022VrFWER5.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will just order more MAX7219s \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"richfiles","CreatedById":129946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T18:29:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMax... MAX!!! NOOOOOOOOO!!!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nLooking good though! You have anything planned for the other 3 columns the MAX7219 chip supports? Is that gonna be other panel lights, or are you ignoring the columns?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-15T18:30:13Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2016 06:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by richfiles\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-15T21:13:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure at the moment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-15T21:14:20Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2016 09:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Krewmember\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-26T23:07:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe annunciator is still on hold do to a lack of parts, but I have been working on other things why I get more parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI finished the translation controller panel \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022aDpGYIH.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/aDpGYIH.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust need to modify the arcade joystick so I can\u00A0push and pull for forward and backward translation \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022b67onvt3rbpftt16a.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://666kb.com/i/b67onvt3rbpftt16a.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI also started work on the main flight stick pedestals. For the flight sticks I\u0027m using Logitech Attack 3\u0027s they are cheap to get and have no twist for yaw, which is good because I\u0027m going to use a set of CH Products Pro Pedals for yaw control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022t1uQ9Oq.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/t1uQ9Oq.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also closed off the pedal compartments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224FVG9Zj.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/4FVG9Zj.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-26T23:09:12Z\u0022 title=\u002205/26/2016 11:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Krewmember\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"richfiles","CreatedById":129946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-27T05:20:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am enjoying being creative and trying to pack as much Apolloishness onto my own desk mounted controller as I can...\u003Cbr\u003E\nStill, it is truly a shame I can\u0027t find the room for something as truly\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eawesome\u003C/em\u003E as your simpit! Keep up the awesome work!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis is a truly inspiring simpit!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-27T15:20:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad I can give some inspiration back to all you awesome people \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"johansen","CreatedById":100198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T00:55:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about sitting horizontal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T02:56:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607385\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464569704\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022100198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022johansen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, johansen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about sitting horizontal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not quite sure what you mean, can you explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"richfiles","CreatedById":129946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T08:46:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe means having the seat laying you on your back, either partially or fully, to simulate a launch position...\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat would be pretty hardcore, but probably not something comfortable for long term play.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"johansen","CreatedById":100198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T13:01:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222607742\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464597997\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129946\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022richfiles\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, richfiles said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe means having the seat laying you on your back, either partially or fully, to simulate a launch position...\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat would be pretty hardcore, but probably not something comfortable for long term play.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could be toggleable haha, i was thinking on the apollo simulators\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krewmember","CreatedById":144837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T14:58:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I see, thank you for clarifying \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess it could be done, but at this point in the build all I can say Is maybe \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeck, if I were to make it go vertical why not just make a full \u003Cem\u003Emotion platform \u003C/em\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Freshmeat","CreatedById":111048,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T20:50:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking good. Someone was working on a translational mode for an arcade joystick, The idea was to place it in an enclosure with rollers and a micro switch front and back, and a spring to make it return to zero. Cannot find it right now, but it might be a way to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stibbons","CreatedById":57865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-30T21:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222608627\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464641423\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Freshmeat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Freshmeat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone was working on a translational mode for an arcade joystick,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe the thread you\u0027re thinking of is this one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/135150-translational-control/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sputnix","CreatedById":141420,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-20T08:00:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222576889\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463045176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Freshmeat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/12/2016 at 7:26 PM, Freshmeat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice work. I have had problems with the MAX chips if the signal is over long wires, the DP pin would not reliably work. It might have been the batch I was working with, but I will recommend hooking up so you do not use it. You have plenty of pins to spare with your setup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222577218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022110719\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463063091\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krewmember\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/13/2016 at 0:24 AM, Krewmember said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the heads up, apparently the MAX7219 can cause electromagnetic interference so maybe that is why \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if this is going to help; I had issues with my 7-segment controllers too (6 in total, all connected together).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can read\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/109163-arduino-ksp_serial_io-odysseus/#comment-2052789\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E about it here\u003C/a\u003E. Or you can \u003Ca href=\u0022https://fabienroyer.wordpress.com/2011/03/13/using-a-max7219max7221-led-display-driver-with-a-netduino/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Equery this post I found\u003C/a\u003E talking about it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn short:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nThere was discussions about SPI and data lengths. These people were trying to run SPI lengths of like 30 feet, or something silly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nAnyway - one commenter mentioned that they \u003Cstrong\u003Etwisted the clock and data lines together to eliminate interference\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nI figured I\u0027d do a test-try to see if this would work. I twisted the cables of both the lines from the 7-segment, and the respective lines from the flex cable - and it works!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\nKeep this in mind if you\u0027re having any issues with GPIO assigned SPI devices!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may help eliminate issues. It did for me! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and excellent work \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s looking amazing! I would definitely go with a fully mobile simpit (if I had time, money, space) - but a fully enclosed experience is just as good! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-20T08:13:46Z\u0022 title=\u002206/20/2016 08:13  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sputnix\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}